	<item>
				<title>FAQ&#039;S</title>
		<link>http://row.lurnglier.com/faq/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 Feb 2014 21:54:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://row.lurnglier.com/?page_id=76</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong>What is the hotel address? </strong>
Row NYC
700 8th Avenue, between 44th and 45th street
New York, NY 10036

<strong>How do we contact the hotel or group sales?</strong>
Hotel: 212-869-3600 or email <a href="info@rownyc.com">info@rownyc.com</a>
Group sales: 646-432-8008 or email <a href="mailto:groupsales@rownyc.com">groupsales@rownyc.com</a>

<strong>Do you have a concierge on site? How do we contact them for Broadway show tickets?</strong>
Yes, we do have a concierge on site and they will be happy to help with Broadway show tickets.

<strong>Concierge Hours:</strong>
Monday through Saturday, 7am – 8am EST
Sunday 8am – 6pm EST
Phone: 646-998-7372
Email: <a href="rownycconcierge@cityexperts.com">rownycconcierge@cityexperts.com</a>

<strong>How do we contact hotel security?</strong>
Call 212-536-1041 or email rownycsecuritylist@rownyc.com

<strong>What is the check-in and checkout time?</strong>
Check-In: 4PM
Checkout: 12 Noon

<strong>What is the tax breakdown charged on your daily rate?</strong>
Our tax breakdown is as follows:
8.8750% NY State Tax
5.8750% NY City Tax
$2.00 NYC Hotel Tax
$1.50 NYS Hotel Tax

<strong>Does Row NYC accept traveler’s checks as payment?</strong>
Yes, the hotel accepts the following as payment: Traveler’s Check, Cashier’s Check and Certified Bank check. Please note that these will be accepted only on arrival. You will still be required to guarantee your booking with a valid credit card. You may also pre-pay with a personal or company check as well - checks mailed within the US must be received 21 business days prior to arrival, and checks mailed from overseas must be received 45 business days prior to arrival.

<strong>Does Row NYC handle packages for guests? Is there a charge for handling packages? </strong>
Row NYC will accept packages for all arriving and in-house guests. Packages should not be sent to the hotel until 3 days prior to the guest’s arrival. Row NYC will apply a $5.00 package handling fee to each item received at the hotel loading dock. All packages should be addressed to the guest name registered on the reservation. Packages that are received without a matching name to the reservation will be held for 3 days before being sent back to sender. All packages received will be sent to guest room upon arrival or during the stay. Row NYC will not store packages throughout the guest stay in our package room. Additional charges may apply.

<strong>Is there a pharmacy or grocery store located nearby?</strong>
Yes:
Duane Reade Pharmacy – Distance from the Row NYC: 2 blocks
661 8th Avenue, New York, NY 10036 (212) 977-1562
The Food Emporium Grocery Store – Distance from the Row NYC: 4 blocks
810 8th Avenue, New York, NY 10019 (212) 977-1710

<strong>Does the hotel have a gift shop? Where is it located and what are the hours?</strong>
Yes. Our gift shop, Iconic M, is located in the lobby past the elevators. Open 24/7, our one-stop-shop for everyday essentials, including a wide range of international magazines and newspapers, snacks, fashionable souvenirs and toiletries.

<strong>Do the guest floors have ice machines?</strong>
Yes. Ice machines are located on the following guest floors: 27, 25, 23, 21, 19, 17, 15, 12, 10, 8, 6 and 4.

<strong>Which is the closest subway station to the hotel?</strong>
The Row NYC is located two short blocks away from the 42nd Street - Port Authority Bus Terminal subway station, where the A, C and E trains are readily accessed. Many entrances to this station are located throughout Times Square - you can choose to walk outside or walk through the station to also access the 1, 2, 3 and 7 trains, as well as the N, Q, R and S trains.

<strong>What are some of the landmarks close to the hotel?</strong>
Hell’s Kitchen, the Theater District, and the Port Authority Bus Terminal are all nearby.

<strong>How far is Times Square?</strong>
Row NYC is one block away from Times Square.

<strong>How far is Rockefeller Center and what can we do there?</strong>
We are about 3 blocks from Rockefeller Center. Rockefeller Center is a complex of 19 commercial buildings covering 22 acres between 48th and 51st streets. Home to NBC studios, the Top of The Rock Observation Deck, and countless shops and restaurants, it is truly a top destination.

<strong>Is there a Macy’s close by?</strong>
The world’s largest department store, Macy’s offers clothing, jewelry, accessories and more for women, men and children in the heart of New York City. Visitors can enjoy 10% savings with their Welcome Savings Pass. It is on 34th Street and 6th Avenue, a short 15 minute walk from the hotel.

<strong>How far is Fifth Avenue and what are some of the stores there?</strong>
New York City’s renowned Fifth Avenue is 4 blocks away. High-end designer stores for men, women and children are all located between 42nd street - 60th street. Notable retailers include: Saks Fifth Avenue, Bergdorf Goodman, Brooks Brothers, Cartier, Gucci, Kenneth Cole, Louis Vuitton, and Tiffany &amp; Co.

<strong>How do we get to the World Trade Center site?</strong>
The World Trade Center site is a short 10 minute cab ride or 20 minute subway ride away from the hotel. By cab, tell the driver that you would like to go to Vesey Street and West Broadway – the World Trade Center Site. By subway, take a downtown E train to the World Trade Center stop. For more information <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/explore-nyc">click here</a>

<strong>How do we get to the Statue of Liberty?</strong>
The Statue of Liberty is accessed through a 10 minute cab ride or 20 minute subway ride from the hotel, and then a 20 minute ferry ride to the Statue of Liberty. By cab, tell the driver that you would like to go to the ferry docks at Battery Park. By subway, take a downtown R train to the Whitehall Street station or a downtown 1 train to the South Ferry station. Next, walk a few short blocks to Battery Park to board the ferry. For ferry information, visit <a href="www.statuecruises.com" target="_blank">www.statuecruises.com</a>. For more information <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/locations/statue-of-liberty-national-monument/">click here</a>

<strong>How far are Chinatown and Little Italy, and what can we do there?</strong>
Chinatown and Little Italy are iconic New York City neighborhoods that are rich with history, shopping and spectacular restaurants. Day or night, they are perfect for taking a stroll and taking in all of the surroundings. The neighborhoods are right next to each other and are a short 10 minute cab ride or 20 minute subway ride from the hotel. By cab, tell the driver to go to Canal Street and Lafayette Street, and that will put you in the middle of it all a few short blocks away. By subway, take a downtown N, Q, or R train to the Canal Street station.

<strong>How far is Central Park?</strong>
New York’s famous Central Park is a short 5 minute cab ride, 10 minute subway ride or 15 minute walk from the hotel. By cab, tell the driver to take you to 59th Street and Columbus Circle, and then enter the park. By subway, take an uptown A or C train to the 59th Street – Columbus Circle stop. If walking, walk outside of the hotel and along 8th Avenue until you get to the park on 59th Street. For more information, <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/locations/central-park/">click here</a>.

<strong>Does the hotel have on-site parking and/or valet parking?</strong>
The hotel does not have on-site parking. Valet parking service is provided by the hotel through Champion Parking Systems, located on 45th street between 7th and 8th Avenue. The valet parking charge for a standard vehicle is $55 for a 24 hour period from the time of arrival and $65 for oversized SUVs for a 24 hour period from the time of arrival. Additional charges may apply if the 24 hour period is exceeded. There are no in/out privileges. Self-parking is also available at Champion Parking Systems, but prices may vary. Please note: valet parking must be requested through a hotel bellman or doorman, as they must create a ticket. After a guest is ready to take their car out, they must stop by the front desk to pay and validate this ticket so it can be given to the garage. If a guest takes their car to the garage themselves, they are responsible for interactions with the garage themselves and the hotel is not responsible.

<strong>Do you have a restaurant in the hotel? Is Breakfast served? What if we need to have a drink? </strong>
Yes. Our restaurant, District M, is a European express café in the AM, serving delicious sweet and savory pastries from NYC’s finest bakeries, including Payard, Balthazar and Pain d’Avignon. In the PM, District M transforms into a chic Neapolitan pizza bar and cocktail lounge, serving hand-stretched pizzas and a curated selection of charcuterie and cheese from New York’s famed Murray’s Cheese Shop. Specialty cocktails, local craft beers and a live music lineup all contribute to an unforgettable evening.

<strong>Breakfast hours: </strong>
Monday – Friday: 6:30am – 11:30am
Saturday – Sunday: 7am – 12pm
<strong>Dinner hours:</strong>
Monday – Sunday: 5pm – 1am

<strong>What are some nearby restaurants? </strong>
New York City is every food lover’s paradise. With thousands of restaurants to choose from - serving everything from mouthwatering local favorites to international delights - you can satisfy just about any craving you have, anytime. Check out some of our favorites <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/explore-nyc/manhattan-restaurants/">here</a> - and contact our concierge to make a reservation for you at any of these spots, or any other restaurant of your choice.
<strong>
Is the hotel pet friendly?</strong>
Pets are not allowed at the hotel.

<strong>What is minimum age required to check in?</strong>
You must be a minimum of 18 years old to check in, along with a valid government issued ID.

<strong>Do you have smoking rooms?</strong>
The hotel is 100% non-smoking. There is a $250 penalty applicable to guests that violate our non-smoking rule.

<strong>What is the hotels’ cancellation policy?</strong>
Cancellations are accepted up to 24 hours prior to arrival date, before 12 noon EST.

<strong>Does the hotel require any kind of deposit prior to checking in?</strong>
Yes. If making the deposit through credit card, it is $100 per stay. If making the deposit through cash, it is $250 per stay. Please note: the hotel system obtains a maximum of 7 night’s worth of credit card authorization, even if a reservation is booked for longer. Authorizations automatically expire after 7 days. While most credit card companies take 5-7 business days to remove the authorization, it also depends on the issuing bank to make it happen and this could take longer. International credit/debit cards might take up to 30 days, depending on their bank.

<strong>Does the hotel pay travel agency commissions?</strong>
Travel agents are paid out a 10% commission as long as a valid IATA number is entered at the time of the reservation.

<strong>Who should we contact if we are group of people wanting to book several rooms, is there a discount?</strong>
We consider 10 rooms, or 10 people or more arriving together, a group. In such cases, there is a mandatory porterage fee (baggage handling fee) that is applicable. For group reservations, please contact Group Sales at groupsales@rownyc.com.

<strong>Does the hotel charge any kind of baggage fees? </strong>
Yes. As of January 2014, our porterage/baggage fee is $8.04 (subject to change without notice) per bag, which equals to $4.02 in &amp; $4.02 out.

<strong>Who do I contact regarding billing?</strong>
Please call the hotel at 888-352-3650 or 212-869-3600 and ask for the Billing department in Accounting. Additionally, you can email accounting at <a href="mailto:KMak@rownyc.com">KMak@rownyc.com</a> or <a href="mailto:NRojas@rownyc.com">NRojas@rownyc.com</a>.

<strong>We are a non-profit agency and are tax exempt, how do we get our tax exempt?</strong>
All guests who are tax exempt will need to bring their own New York City and state tax exempt forms, duly signed along with themselves. The hotel does not provide these. These forms may also be faxed directly to our accounting office at 212-703-0640, with the confirmation number and name of the guest. In addition to providing tax exempt documents, the tax exempt organization must pay for the stay in order for it to be tax exempt. This can either be prepaid with the organization’s credit card (CC authorization form) or a check can be sent from the organization at least 10 days prior to check-in. Payment for the room charge will then be applied and tax exemption set in the hotel system so taxes are not run. If the stay is not prepaid and guest claims tax exemption at check-in, they need to present the tax exempt documents and the exempt organization’s CC that belongs to the guest on arrival. If the guest paid on their own without a tax exempt form or pre-payment on arrival, the guest has a 90 day window after check-out to present proof of tax exemption and payment from the organization (CC authorization form). Once it is received and payment is applied, the hotel will refund the guest’s charge in full.

<strong>Can we pre-pay for our reservation and what is the procedure?</strong>
All credit card authorizations need to be faxed to the reservations department at 212-703-0644, with only the last four digits of the credit card and a contact number. Once it is received, we may call to obtain the full number. Email is not accepted and will be deleted to ensure safety of your credit card and our compliance with PCI regulations.

<strong>Does the hotel have amenities like a business center, fitness studio or pool?</strong>
Yes. Our state-of-the-art Internet lounge ensures that guests stay connected – in style. Under a 24 foot glass wall overlooking the electric energy of 8th Avenue, guests can enjoy 30 minutes of complimentary use with the option to purchase additional time. Password protected remote printing is also available, allowing guests to print documents securely and conveniently from their room. Open 24/7, our fitness studio keeps guests energized in the city that never sleeps with top-of-the line treadmills and elliptical machines, as well as free weights and recumbent bicycles. The hotel does not have a pool.

<strong>How many rooms does the hotel have?</strong>
The hotel has 1331 rooms.

<strong>How many guest floors does the hotel have?</strong>
The hotel has 28 floors, with guest floors starting on the 3rd floor.
Is there ATM in the hotel in case we need to withdraw cash?
Yes, there is an ATM in the lobby for your convenience.
<strong>
Does the hotel provide any WiFi services and are they free?</strong>
The hotel does have wireless internet service at $14.95 for 24 hours, inclusive of taxes per room.

<strong>Does the hotel have baggage/luggage holding area and is there a charge?</strong>
We do have a complimentary luggage holding area. As per our policy, we allow guests to store luggage only during their stay. In case a guest is checking out on a particular date and returning a day/s later, we will not be able to store luggage. The same applies in case the luggage arrives a day or more prior to guest arrival. For any further questions please contact the bell desk.

<strong>Does the hotel have a courtesy shuttle from and to local airports?</strong>
The hotel does not have a courtesy shuttle, but the concierge can assist with all your travel needs. Call our concierge at 646-998-7372, or email rownycconcierge@cityexperts.com.
<strong>
Do you have any meeting or banquet space?</strong>
The hotel does not have any meeting or banquet space.

<strong>Does the hotel offer any rooms for the disabled?</strong>
Yes, the hotel has ADA accessible rooms for the disabled.

<strong>What is the square footage of your hotel rooms?</strong>
Standard – Full &amp; Queen Bed/ 125-135 sq. ft.
Superior – Full &amp; Queen Bed/ 135-165 sq. ft., Twin Beds/ 160 sq. ft., 2 Double Beds/ 210 sq. ft., King Bed/ 235 sq. ft., ADA Full &amp; Queen Beds/ 325 sq. ft., ADA KING &amp; Twin Beds/ 375 sq. ft. and ADA 2 Double Beds/ 350 sq. ft.
Deluxe City View – Full &amp; Queen Bed/155-170 sq. ft., Twin Beds/160 sq. ft., 2 Double Beds/210 sq. ft., King Bed/ 235 sq. ft.
Premium City View – Queen Bed/ 185 sq. ft., 2 Double Beds/ 210 sq. ft., King Bed/235 sq. ft.
Executive Suite – Separate Bedroom with King Bed and Living Room/ 360 sq. ft.

Penthouse Suite – King sized beds and en suite baths with luxurious showers and soaking tubs. Both suites offer an additional bedroom option with either two double beds or one king bed in the adjoining room. / 775 sq. ft. For Penthouse suite reservations, please email us at info@rownyc.com.
<strong>
Does the hotel offer housekeeping services?</strong>
Yes, the hotel offers complimentary housekeeping services.

<strong>Can we get our clothes laundered or dry cleaned during our stay?</strong>
Yes. A pick-up request for laundry or dry cleaning must be called in before 9am if guests require delivery by that evening. Any requests after 9am will be delivered the next day. Please note: our laundry and dry cleaning is contracted to an outside company not on premises and is not managed by the hotel.

<strong>Do you have central air? </strong>
Yes, the hotel has central air.

<strong>Does the hotel provide child cribs, is there a charge?</strong>
Yes, the hotel provides complimentary child cribs.
<strong>
What if we have an unexpected guest? Do you provide and roll away beds?</strong>
No, the hotel does not provide roll away beds.

<strong>Do all have refrigerators?</strong>
Refrigerators are in select rooms and are also available by request for $20.00 per stay – subject to availability.

<strong>Do you have rooms with a view?</strong>
Yes – we have two categories of rooms with views – Deluxe City View room and Premium City View. These rooms are not guaranteed unless you have specifically reserved one. For more information, <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/hotel-rooms-times-square-new-york/">click here</a>.

<strong>What was the hotel know as prior to the Row NYC? </strong>
The Row NYC hotel was originally designed in 1928 by Herbert J. Knapp - theater architect extraordinaire - and has remained its own dramatic New York icon ever since. Throughout the last century, this striking hotel has starred as the Lincoln, the Manhattan, and the Milford Plaza before making its much-anticipated debut as the Row NYC.

<strong>How close is Row NYC to Broadway Theaters or the Theater District?</strong>
The hotel is just one block to the Theater District.

<strong>What can you tell me about the Theater District?</strong>
Manhattan’s Theater District is where you’ll find all the famous Broadway plays you’ve always wanted to see. This area is also loaded with a wonderful array of NYC shops, restaurants and attractions. For more information, <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/explore-nyc/time-square-attractions/">click here</a>.

<strong>
How close is Row NYC to Radio City Music Hall?</strong>
The hotel is just 5 blocks to New York City’s famed Radio City Music Hall. Radio City Music Hall is an entertainment venue located in Rockefeller Center. Nicknamed “The Showplace of the Nation”, it was declared a landmark in 1978 and has hosted some of the world’s most-recognized musicians and acts, including its signature Radio City Christmas Spectacular – featuring the New York Rockettes.

<strong>What can you tell us about NYC Shopping and Woodbury Commons Shopping Outlets?</strong>
Many regard NYC as not only the center of the universe, but the verifiable shopping capital of the world. From world class designers to ready-to-wear favorites, NYC has it all - and then some. For more information, <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/explore-nyc/shopping-guide/">click here</a>. One of the world’s premier shopping destinations, Woodbury Common Premium Outlet is an exquisite collection of shops with the finest designer labels and brands – at an incredible discount. Located just over 1 hour from New York City, Woodbury Common Premium Outlet is a bargain shopper’s dream. Our concierge can have tickets arranged for daily tours to Woodbury Commons – call our concierge at 646-998-7372, or email <a href="rownycconcierge@cityexperts.com" target="_blank">rownycconcierge@cityexperts.com</a>.

<strong>What can you tell me about NYC’s Financial District?</strong>
The hotel location is a spectacular alternative for those who need to work in NYC’s Financial District, but want to be where the action is. It is a short 10 minute cab ride or 20 minute train ride to the Financial District from the hotel.

<strong>Why should I stay at ROW NYC?</strong>
The Row NYC hotel has pioneered a new era of individuality by meeting NYC’s signature urban grit with grandeur - transforming your stay into a completely contemporary experience – with a front row view to Times Square that’s truly incomparable. Our guests reside in the middle of it all, with the excitement of 24/7 access to everything and anything that NYC is known for – right at their doorstep.

<strong>How close are you to Broadway?</strong>
The hotel is one block away from Broadway.

<strong>What kinds of bathroom amenities are provided in your rooms?</strong>
We provide the following PURE products in all our rooms: Shampoo, Lotion, Bath Soap, Face Soap &amp; Shower Cap, along with a hair dryer.

<strong>What can you tell us about the more popular New York City Neighborhoods?</strong>
For more information, <a href="http://www.rownyc.com/explore-nyc/">click here</a>.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Privacy</title>
		<link>http://row.lurnglier.com/privacy-policy/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 Feb 2014 21:55:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://row.lurnglier.com/?page_id=81</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[The Milford Plaza New York Hotel is a midtown Manhattan Hotel in New York City. Our classical, European designed Manhattan Hotel is located in the heart of Manhattan, close to Business and Leisure Attractions. Our Manhattan Hotel provides our Hotel Guests with a perfect mix of comfortable Guest Rooms, ideal New York City location and great Hotel Guest Services all at a very affordable rate that will surprise you.

INTRODUCTION: We have a strong commitment to providing excellent service to all of our customers, including respecting their concerns about privacy. We understand that visitors to our website may have questions about whether and how this website collects and uses information. Accordingly, we have prepared this statement to inform you of our privacy principles. Use of this website by you will be deemed as your acknowledgment and acceptance of this privacy statement.

BROWSING: Visitors who browse this website do so on an anonymous basis. We have not configured this website to collect any information from your computer without your input. This means that, unless you voluntarily and knowingly provide us with information, we will not know your identity, your e-mail address, or any other information identifiable to you

INTERNET PROTOCOL (IP) ADDRESS: An IP address is a number that is automatically assigned to your computer every time you browse the Internet. When users request a page from our site, our servers log the user's current IP address. We use IP addresses to help diagnose problems. We do not link IP addresses to anything personally identifiable. Thus, each user session is anonymous

INFORMATION: When we need to collect information from you, we will ask you to voluntarily supply us with the information we need. For example, if you would like to make a reservation at one of our hotels, we will ask you for information such as name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, credit card type, credit card number, expiration date and room preference (non-smoking room or no preference) to process your reservation. We will use your e-mail address to send a confirmation and, if necessary, might use the other information to contact you for help to process the reservation.

When we ask you for personal data when making a reservation or purchasing a gift certificate, including your name, address and credit card data, it is transferred over a Secured Sockets Layer (SSL) line provided you are using a SSL enabled browser such as Microsoft Internet Explorer or Netscape Navigator. This ensures that your information is encrypted as it travels over the Internet. This secure mode is enabled before any such information is transmitted from your computer. You will know you are in secure mode when the padlock icon in the lower right hand corner of the computer screen appears in the locked position. In addition, when accessing a secure server, the first characters of the site address with change from "http" to "https". After information reaches us it is stored on a secure server that resides behind a firewall that is designed to block access from outside the Company.

We may also ask you to fill out an online customer survey, to obtain your suggestions or comments about your use of our services, or for similar purposes. Providing this information is voluntary. We also, at times, may use an interactive dialogue product to assist visitors while on certain web pages. The content of the dialogue is not identifiable to you unless you voluntarily provide us with your name or other information regarding your identity. The dialogue product is used only to facilitate your visit by providing the additional information you request, and the content will not be stored and used by us except for quality assurance and statistical analysis purposes, so that we can better anticipate our prospective customers' needs.

COOKIES: Like many companies, from time to time we may use "cookie" technology on our Site. When you visit our site, the cookie tells us whether you've visited us before or are a new visitor, where you were referred from and also tells us if you booked. The cookie does not track any personal information about you or provide us with any way to contact you, and the cookie does not extract any information from your computer.

USE OF INFORMATION: We treat the information you provide to us as confidential information; it is, accordingly, subject to our company's security procedures and strict corporate policies regarding protection and use of confidential information. Because laws applicable to personal information vary by country, our hotels or other business operations may put in place additional measures that vary depending on the applicable legal requirements. Information is generally processed and stored in the United States, in which data protection laws are not as comprehensive as in the European Union. Information gathered is used only for the purpose for which the information was collected and is not used or shared with other companies. The personal information you provide to us for making a reservation is made available to the applicable hotel for the purpose of meeting your reservation request. If you cancel your reservation, the information is stored for record keeping purposes only and is not accessed again. After completing your stay the information you provide may be used for direct marketing our hotel. We may use the services of a third party mail house for the sole purpose of mailing materials.

DISCLOSURE OF INFORMATION &amp; OPT-OUT: We will not sell, trade, rent or release such information to entities outside of the family of hotels, for their use without your approval and giving you the opportunity to opt-out.

LINKS TO OTHER SITES: If you choose to leave this site via links to other hotel sites, including those of advertisers, we are not responsible for the privacy policies or content of those sites, nor are we responsible for the cookies those sites might deposit on your hard drive.

MINORS: Our web sites do not sell products for purchase by children. If you are under 18, you may only use our web sites with the involvement of a parent or guardian.

LEGAL ISSUES: We will disclose personal information when required by law or in good faith belief if such action is necessary or desirable to comply with the law, protect or defend the rights or property of our hotels, the site or its users.

PRIVACY STATEMENT CHANGES: In the future, we may need to change the privacy statement for our properties. All changes will be made here so that you will always know what information we gather, how we might use that information and whether we will disclose it to anyone. Changes in the privacy statement will only affect our treatment of information supplied by you to us following the effective date of such changes, i.e., for information supplied by you prior to the change in the privacy statement, we will continue to honor the obligations of the privacy statement, for such information, in effect when the information was originally supplied by you. Information entered or re-entered following a change in the privacy statement will be governed by the new privacy statement.

CONCLUSION: Your privacy concerns are important to us. We hope this privacy statement has been helpful to you.

If you have any questions about this privacy statement or privacy concerns please contact us.

Visiting New York? Choose Milford Plaza Hotel - A Times Square Hotel.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Hotel</title>
		<link>http://row.lurnglier.com/times-square-hotels/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2014 17:08:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://row.lurnglier.com/?page_id=353</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Meet the Row NYC hotel. 

The Row NYC hotel has pioneered a new era of individuality by meeting NYC’s signature urban grit with grandeur - transforming your stay into a completely contemporary experience – with a front row view to Times Square that’s truly incomparable. Our guests undeniably reside in the middle of it all, with exciting access to everything and anything – 24/7.

Located in the heart of Times Square, the Row NYC hotel was originally designed in 1928 by Herbert J. Knapp - theater architect extraordinaire - and has remained its own dramatic New York icon ever since. Throughout the last century, this striking hotel has starred as the Lincoln, the Manhattan, and the Milford Plaza before making its much-anticipated debut as the Row NYC.  

Endlessly lounge-worthy, the Row NYC flaunts a spectacular lobby and statement spaces, artfully adorned in sleek stainless steel, wood and glass. Signature New York City inspired artworks enliven the senses and atmosphere throughout, from an animated light sculpture by video artist Yorgo Alexopolus, to a digital art gallery featuring famed paparazzo Ron Gallela’s most infamous shots from city nights that never end, to street artist photography installations within guest room floors. 

Inspired amenities abound at the Row NYC. Our restaurant, <District M>, is a European express café by day and a Neapolitan pizza bar and cocktail lounge by night, offering a curated selection of delicious food, coffee, cocktails and more – sourced from some of NYC’s finest eateries. Open 24/7, <Iconic M> is a one-stop-shop for everyday essentials with a twist. And, our state-of-the-art Internet lounge always keeps our guests connected – in style.
The Row NYC boasts 1331 contemporary guest rooms on 28 floors, flaunting chic, Manhattan-inspired decor in white-hot hues mixed with unexpectedly vibrant custom furnishings. 

Ready to create your New York City?

]]></content:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[How would you create your New York City? Start with your Times Square hotel.

The heart of Manhattan. 24/7 anything and everything.

You'll have a front row view to the middle of it all –

and you wouldn't want it any other way.

Next, an influential place where of-the-moment urban design, art, culture and taste conquer all.

Must-haves? An endlessly lounge-worthy lobby &amp; statement spaces,

artfully adorned (of course) in sleek stainless steel, wood and glass.

Positively plush rooms made for unwinding in your NYC hotel –

boasting white-hot hues &amp; Manhattan-inspired décor.

Throw in a walking tour at every corridor through street artist photography,

tantalizing NYC sourced eats and a cocktail (or three) for good measure.
Now, things are really rolling –

and not only because the nearest subway is across the street.

Ready to get started?

Welcome to a Time Square hotel<i> </i>that's more New York than New York – the Row NYC.

				<title>Sample Page</title>
		<link>http://row.lurnglier.com/sample-page/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 10 Feb 2014 14:15:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://row.lurnglier.com/wordpress/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

<blockquote>Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>

...or something like this:

<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>

As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://row.lurnglier.com/wordpress/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!]]></content:encoded>

Present your Eat &amp; Play Card to any of the over 100 participating businesses (complete list available at front desk). You’ll receive instant discounts of 10% - 50% off your entire bill, making it easy to save over $100 each day.*

Participating Eat &amp; Play Card businesses include:

• Heartland Brewery

• McCormick and Schmick’s

• B. Smith’s

• Sky Room, Bourbon Street

• Lindy’s

• McDonald’s

• Famous Footwear

• Guggenheim Museum

• NHL Store

• Intrepid Museum

• TGI Friday’s

• Legend’s Bar

• Shula’s Steakhouse

• Charley O’s

• Delmonico’s

• Macy’s

• DeNatale Jewelers

• Central Park Zoo

• NY Skyride

*Eat &amp; Play Card is valid for up to 4 people and for 30 days (from first use).]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Row NYC New York Shopping Spectacular Package</title>
		<link>http://row.lurnglier.com/?post_type=specials&#038;p=571</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2014 19:27:28 +0000</pubDate>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Save 10% off the best available rate and receive round-trip luxury bus tickets to Woodbury Common Premium Outlets for each paying guest per trip.* 
*Valued at $42 per adult and $21 per child, age 3-11.

Details:

Shopping Trip Length: Approximate travel time from Manhattan to Woodbury Common Premium Outlet is a scenic 1 hour ride in a luxurious and comfortable bus provided by Gray Line, which is New York’s largest and reliable bus company. Bus transportation includes a complimentary VIP Coupon Book (valued at $10) with hundreds of dollars in additional savings.

Shopping Trip Departure: Your luxury bus departs from the Port Authority Bus Terminal Gray Line Office on 8th Avenue & 42nd Street - Ground Level Entrance. The Row NYC is located on 8th Avenue & 44th Street - just 2 blocks away from the Port Authority. Walk time is just 5 minutes.

Shopping Trip Schedule: Trips are available 7 days a week. Bus seating is available on a first come, first served basis.

Additionally, Woodbury Common Premium Outlet caters to international visitors and employs a staff of interpreters, foreign currency exchange and foreign shipping services. As a result, visitors are able to shop and ship purchases back home - directly from Woodbury Common Premium Outlet!

Woodbury Common Premium Outlet 
498 Red Apple Court 
Central Valley, NY 10917 
(845) 928-4000
Open daily: 10:00am - 9:00pm
